@page
@model HealthcareSupport.CaseEvaluation.Pages.Account.ConfirmUserModel
@*
    Custom Razor view for /Account/ConfirmUser. Filesystem precedence
    overrides the Pro framework's stock ConfirmUser page. The paired
    PageModel 302s to /Account/Login on every request; this view body
    is never rendered (the redirect fires before the view runs) but
    exists so the file-based route handler picks up our PageModel.

    Why the redirect: unverified-email login state is absorbed into
    Login + the always-visible Resend verification link below the form
    (B-3, proposed-copy.md 2.4). The dedicated ConfirmUser page is no
    longer reachable through the project's auth flow, but a stale
    bookmark or old email reference still bounces here -- 302 to Login
    keeps the user moving forward.
*@
